HEADWORD: Phthalin
<hw>Phthal"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
colorless crystalline substance obtained by reduction from phthalein,
into which it is easily converted by oxidation; hence, any one of the
series of which phthalin proper is the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phthalyl</ent>⟦br⟧
